						<a name="465449"></a>
						<div class="comment yellow">
							<div class="comment-body">
								<p>@Elyse</p>

<p>Ricotta made from way is done the exact same way: heat, and add acid.</p>

<p>The whey must be leftover from a rennet-coagulated cheese though (i.e. you can't make more ricotta from the whey you just got from making ricotta).</p>

<p>Yield will be significantly smaller.</p>
								<div class="comment-body-bottom"></div>
							</div>
							<p class="commenter postFooter"><a href="http://www.seriouseats.com/user/profile/GoodEaterKenji">J. Kenji Lopez-Alt</a> at <a href="http://www.seriouseats.com/2010/02/how-to-make-fresh-ricotta-fast-easy-homemade-cheese-the-food-lab.html#465449"> 2:20PM on 03/09/10</a></p>
