						</div><!-- close comment -->
					
						<a name="465837"></a>
						<div class="comment yellow">
							<div class="comment-body">
								<p>@biabiaboiler</p>

<p>The ratio is 1:16  (1 tablespoon per cup) no matter how much you do. Although depending on how old your milk is, it may vary a little bit. Start with slightly less than you need, then if it doesn't curdle after heating, add a little at a time until it does.</p>
								<div class="comment-body-bottom"></div>
							</div>
							<p class="commenter postFooter"><a href="http://www.seriouseats.com/user/profile/GoodEaterKenji">J. Kenji Lopez-Alt</a> at <a href="http://www.seriouseats.com/2010/02/how-to-make-fresh-ricotta-fast-easy-homemade-cheese-the-food-lab.html#465837">12:16AM on 03/10/10</a></p>
